                    "sub_headline": "A vibrant stretch of golden sand lined with world-class resorts, bustling night markets, and endless aquatic activities.",
                    "detailed_description": "Batu Ferringhi is the most famous beach in Penang, offering a long expanse of fine, white sand along the northern coast of the island. By day, it's a hub for water sports, from parasailing and jet-skiing to windsurfing. The beachfront is dotted with international-standard hotels and restaurants. As the sun sets, the area transforms into a lively open-air night market where visitors can find a variety of souvenirs, local crafts, and delicious street food. The scenic view of the Andaman Sea, especially during sunset, makes it a picturesque destination for both relaxation and recreation.",
