                    "headline": "A Serene Seaside Suburb with a Picturesque Shoreline",
                    "sub_headline": "Escape the main crowds and enjoy the tranquil waters, home to the iconic floating mosque and various water sports clubs.",
                    "detailed_description": "Situated between the city proper and Batu Ferringhi, Tanjung Bungah offers a more relaxed beach experience. Once a sleepy fishing village, it has grown into a charming suburb with a mix of modern high-rises and traditional houses. The beach is known for its relatively calm waters, making it a favorite for swimming and kayaking. A major landmark is the Penang Floating Mosque (Masjid Terapung), which offers a stunning sight, especially during high tide. The Penang Water Sports Centre is also located here, offering activities for enthusiasts.",
