                    "headline": "A Pristine Nature Reserve with a Unique Meromictic Lake",
                    "sub_headline": "Located within the Penang National Park, this secluded beach is a sanctuary for green turtles and features a rare lake where salt and fresh water don't mix.",
                    "detailed_description": "Pantai Kerachut is a remote and beautiful beach accessible via a jungle trail through the Penang National Park or by boat. It is famous for two unique natural phenomena: a meromictic lake, where layers of freshwater and seawater do not mix, and as a nesting ground for Green Sea Turtles. A turtle sanctuary and hatchery is located at one end of the beach to protect the eggs and educate visitors. Its untouched beauty and tranquil atmosphere make it a perfect destination for nature lovers and those seeking solitude.",
