                    "headline": "A Secluded Paradise on Tioman's Eastern Coast",
                    "sub_headline": "A long, beautiful stretch of golden sand, known for its tranquil vibe, surf-worthy waves, and vital turtle conservation project.",
                    "detailed_description": "Juara Beach is a remote village and beach on the eastern side of Tioman Island, accessible by a 4WD vehicle across the island's central mountain range. This seclusion gives it a wonderfully untouched and peaceful atmosphere. The beach is divided into two parts by a small headland and is one of the best places on Tioman for surfing during the monsoon season. It is also home to the Juara Turtle Project, a vital conservation effort for sea turtles. With a handful of charming chalets and restaurants, it's the perfect escape for those looking to disconnect and enjoy nature.",
